50enum class ExprPrecedence : int {
51 /*! \brief Identity(e.g., IntImm, Var) and function call(e.g., floordiv, min) */
52 kIdentity = 0,
53 /*!
54 * \brief Multiplication(*), division(/), and remainder(%)
55 * \note floorDiv, floorMod is marked as kIdentity since they are function calls.
56 */
57 kMultiplicationDivision = 1,
58 /*! \brief Addition(+) and subtraction(-) */
59 kAdditionSubtraction = 2,
60 /*! \brief For relational operators < and <= and > and >= respectively */
61 kRelational = 3,
62 /*! \brief For equality operators = and != respectively */
63 kEquality = 4,
64 /*! \brief And(&&) */
65 kAnd = 5,
66 /*! \brief Or(||) */
67 kOr = 6,
68 /*! \brief Unknown precedence */
69 kUnknown = 7,
70};
71
72/*! \brief Utility used for identifying usage of a buffer_var
73 *
74 * \details Find the Buffer object that corresponds to a variable or
75 * allocation, based on the BufferLoad/BufferStore instances that
76 * occur within the allocation's body.
77 */
78class BufferUsageFinder : public StmtExprVisitor {
79 public:
80 static Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> FindUsage(Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage, Stmt body) {
81 BufferUsageFinder visitor(std::move(usage));
82 visitor.VisitStmt(body);
83 return std::move(visitor.usage_);
84 }
85
86 void VisitExpr_(const VarNode* op) final {
87 Var var = GetRef<Var>(op);
88 if (!usage_.count(var)) {
89 usage_.Set(var, {});
90 }
91 }
92
93 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
94 VisitBuffer(op->buffer);
95 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
96 }
97
98 void VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) final {
99 VisitBuffer(op->buffer);
100 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
101 }
102
103 private:
104 explicit BufferUsageFinder(Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage) : usage_(usage) {}
105
106 void VisitBuffer(const Buffer& buffer) {
107 if (buffers_visited_.count(buffer.get())) {
108 return;
109 }
110 buffers_visited_.insert(buffer.get());
111
112 Array<Buffer> arr = usage_.Get(buffer->data).value_or({});
113 arr.push_back(buffer);
114 usage_.Set(buffer->data, arr);
115 }
116
117 // The search result.
118 Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage_;
119 // The buffers that have been visited so far, to avoid duplicate
120 // entries in the search result.
121 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> buffers_visited_;
122};

301 /*! Helper functions for loop printing. */
302 /*!
303 * \brief Print a single for loop
304 * \param loop The for loop to be printed
305 */
306 virtual Doc PrintLoop(const For& loop);
307 /*! \brief Print all simple loops in stack into one line using tir_prefix_.grid(). */
308 Doc PrintLoopStack();
309 /*!
310 * \brief Check whether a loop satisfies:
311 * 1. the loop is serial;
312 * 2. the loop has no annotation;
313 * 3. the loop starts from 0;
314 * 4. there is no optional information.
315 * \param for_op the for node to be checked
316 * \return A boolean indicating whether the input loop satisfies the above conditions
317 */
318 bool IsSimpleLoop(const ForNode* for_op) {
319 return for_op->kind == ForKind::kSerial && for_op->annotations.empty() &&
320 is_zero(for_op->min) && !ContainsOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(for_op));
321 }
322 /*!
323 * \brief Check whether the `min` or `extent` of a loop depends on previous loops
324 * \param for_op The loop to be checked
325 * \return A boolean indicating whether the input loop depends on previous loops
326 */
327 bool DependOnPrevLoops(const ForNode* for_op) {
328 auto f_check = [&var_map = this->loop_var_map_](const VarNode* v) { return var_map.count(v); };
329 return UsesVar(for_op->min, f_check) || UsesVar(for_op->extent, f_check);
330 }

333 * \brief Print additional info about expr in comment.
334 * \param expr The expression.
335 */
336 Doc PrintOptionalInfo(const Stmt& stmt) {
337 Doc doc;
338 // default annotations
339 if (ContainsOptionalInfo(stmt)) {

344 }

346 /*!
347 * \brief special method to render vectors of docs with a separator
348 * \param vec vector of docs
349 * \param sep separator
350 */
351 static Doc PrintSep(const std::vector<Doc>& vec, const Doc& sep) {
352 Doc seq;
353 if (vec.size() != 0) {
354 seq = vec[0];
355 for (size_t i = 1; i < vec.size(); i++) {
356 seq << sep << vec[i];
357 }
358 }
359 return seq;
360 }

362 /*!
363 * \brief dump meta info
364 * \return Doc with meta info
365 */
366 Doc DumpMeta() {
367 if (show_meta_) {
368 return Doc::Text("__tvm_meta__ = ")

375 /*!
376 * \brief special method to print out data type
377 * \param dtype The data type
378 */
379 static Doc PrintDType(DataType dtype) {
380 return Doc::StrLiteral(runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype));
381 }
382
383 /*!
384 * \brief special method to print out const scalar
385 * \param dtype The data type
386 * \param data The pointer to hold the data.
387 */
388 template <typename T>
389 Doc PrintConstScalar(DataType dtype, const T* data) const {
390 Doc doc;
391 std::ostringstream os;
392 if (dtype.is_float() || dtype.is_float16() || dtype.is_bfloat16()) {
393 os.precision(17);
394 }
395 os << data[0];
396 if (dtype == DataType::Int(32)) {
397 doc << Doc::Text(os.str());
398 } else if (dtype == DataType::Bool()) {
399 doc << Doc::Text(data[0] ? "True" : "False");
400 } else {
401 doc << tir_prefix_ << "." << runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype) << "(" << Doc::Text(os.str())
402 << ")";
403 }
404 return doc;
405 }
406
407 public:
408 static Doc PrintHeader(const std::string& tir_prefix) {
409 Doc header;
410 if (tir_prefix != "tir") {
411 header << "# from tvm.script import tir as " << tir_prefix << Doc::NewLine();
412 } else {
413 header << "# from tvm.script import tir" << Doc::NewLine();
414 }
415 return header;
416 }
417};

419/*!
420 * \brief special method to print NDArray in TIR
421 * \param arr the NDArray to be printed
422 * \param os the output stream where the NDArray will be printed to
423 */
424template <typename T>
425void NDArrayToTIR(::tvm::runtime::NDArray arr, std::ostream& os) {
426 int ndim = arr->ndim;
427 int tot_dim = 1;
428 for (int i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
429 tot_dim *= arr->shape[i];
430 }
431 T* data_ptr = reinterpret_cast<T*>(arr->data);
432 os << "[";
433 for (int i = 0; i < tot_dim; i++) {
434 os << (i != 0 ? ", " : "") << data_ptr[i];
435 }
436 os << "]";
437}

439Doc TVMScriptPrinter::GetUniqueName(std::string prefix) {
440 std::replace(prefix.begin(), prefix.end(), '.', '_');
441 std::string unique_prefix = prefix;
442 auto it = name_alloc_map_.find(prefix);
443 if (it != name_alloc_map_.end() && it->second >= 0) {
444 while (name_alloc_map_.count(unique_prefix = prefix + "_" + std::to_string(++it->second)) > 0) {
445 }
446 }
447 name_alloc_map_[unique_prefix] = 0;
448 return Doc::Text(unique_prefix);
449}

451Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocVar(const Var& var) {
452 const auto& it = memo_var_.find(var);
453 if (it != memo_var_.end()) {
454 return it->second;
455 }
456 std::string name = var->name_hint.operator std::string();
457 if (name.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name[0])) {
458 name = "v" + name;
459 }
460 Doc val = GetUniqueName(name);
461 memo_var_[var] = val;
462 return val;
463}
464
465Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocBufferDeclaration(const Buffer& buf) {
466 Doc doc = Print(buf->shape);
467 bool print_factor_explicitly = false;
468 doc << ", dtype=" << PrintDType(buf->dtype);
469 if (memo_var_.find(buf->data) != memo_var_.end()) {
470 doc << ", data=" << Print(buf->data);
471 } else {
472 // implicitly define data
473 memo_var_[buf->data] = Doc::Text(memo_buf_[buf].str() + ".data");
474 var_not_in_headers_.insert(buf->data.get());
475 }
476 if (!buf->strides.empty()) {
477 doc << ", strides=" << Print(buf->strides);
478 }
479 if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<VarNode>()) {
480 Var elem_offset = Downcast<Var>(buf->elem_offset);
481 if (memo_var_.find(elem_offset) != memo_var_.end()) {
482 doc << ", elem_offset=" << Print(buf->elem_offset);
483 } else {
484 // implicitly define elem_offset
485 memo_var_[elem_offset] = Doc::Text(memo_buf_[buf].str() + ".elem_offset");
486 var_not_in_headers_.insert(elem_offset.get());
487 print_factor_explicitly = true;
488 }
489 } else if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
490 IntImm elem_offset = Downcast<IntImm>(buf->elem_offset);
491 if (elem_offset->value != 0) {
492 doc << ", elem_offset=" << Print(buf->elem_offset);
493 }
494 }
495 if (buf.scope() != "global") {
496 doc << ", scope=" << Doc::StrLiteral(buf.scope());
497 }
498 if (buf->data_alignment != runtime::kAllocAlignment) {
499 doc << ", align=" << buf->data_alignment;
500 }
501 if (buf->offset_factor != 1 || print_factor_explicitly) {
502 doc << ", offset_factor=" << buf->offset_factor;
503 }
504 if (buf->buffer_type != BufferType::kDefault) {
505 doc << ", type=" << Doc::StrLiteral("auto");
506 }
507 if (buf->axis_separators.size()) {
508 doc << ", axis_separators=" << Print(buf->axis_separators);
509 }
510 return doc;
511}
512
513Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocBuf(const Buffer& buffer) {
514 const auto& it = memo_buf_.find(buffer);
515 if (it != memo_buf_.end()) {
516 return it->second;
517 }
518 std::string name = buffer->name;
519 if (name.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name[0])) {
520 name = "buf_" + name;
521 }
522 Doc val = GetUniqueName(name);
523 memo_buf_[buffer] = val;
524 memo_buf_decl_[buffer] = AllocBufferDeclaration(buffer);
525 return val;
526}

528/*!
529 * \brief Check if any optional information exists in annotate_ for
530 * a given Stmt.
531 * \param stmt The statement.
532 */
533bool TVMScriptPrinter::ContainsOptionalInfo(const Stmt& stmt) {
534 if (annotate_ == nullptr) return false;
535 return !annotate_(stmt).empty();
536}

538/*!
539 * \brief Try to dealloc vars out of space and leave the index to coming vars.
540 * \note It is not a necessary step.
541 */
542void TVMScriptPrinter::TryDeallocVar(const Var& var) {
543 auto it = memo_var_.find(var);
544 ICHECK(it != memo_var_.end());
545 std::string print_name = it->second.str();
546
547 std::string name_hint = var->name_hint.operator std::string();
548 if (name_hint.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name_hint[0])) {
549 name_hint = "v" + name_hint;
550 }
551 std::replace(name_hint.begin(), name_hint.end(), '.', '_');
552
553 auto it2 = name_alloc_map_.find(name_hint);
554 // Skip it if we can not find the name_hint in name_alloc_map_.
555 if (it2 == name_alloc_map_.end()) return;
556 if (it2->second > 0) {
557 name_hint = name_hint + '_' + std::to_string(it2->second);
558 }
559 // Skip it if the name_hint is not equal to how it should be printed.
560 if (name_hint != print_name) return;
561 // Free the conresponding name_alloc_map_ index
562 --it2->second;
563}
564
565Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintMatchBufferRegion(const MatchBufferRegionNode* op) {
566 const Buffer& buf = op->buffer;
567 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
568
569 Doc doc = Print(op->buffer) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".match_buffer(" << Print(op->source)
570 << ", " << memo_buf_decl_[op->buffer] << ")";
571 return doc;
572}
573
574// check if all arguments, except the first two, are specified for T.match_buffer
575// if not, then this match buffer is printed out as T.buffer in prim_func arguments
576// and check whether there are undefined variables in the shape/strides.
577bool TVMScriptPrinter::IsSimpleBuffer(const Buffer& buf) {
578 if (memo_var_.find(buf->data) != memo_var_.end()) {
579 return false;
580 }
581 if (!buf->strides.empty()) {
582 return false;
583 }
584 for (const PrimExpr& shp_i : buf->shape) {
585 if (!UndefinedVars(shp_i).empty()) {
586 return false;
587 }
588 }
589 for (const PrimExpr& stride_i : buf->strides) {
590 if (!UndefinedVars(stride_i).empty()) {
591 return false;
592 }
593 }
594 if (!UndefinedVars(buf->elem_offset).empty()) {
595 return false;
596 } else if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
597 IntImm elem_offset = Downcast<IntImm>(buf->elem_offset);
598 if (elem_offset->value != 0) {
599 return false;
600 }
601 }
602 if (buf.scope() != "global") {
603 return false;
604 }
605 if (buf->data_alignment != runtime::kAllocAlignment) {
606 return false;
607 }
608 if (buf->offset_factor != 1) {
609 return false;
610 }
611 if (buf->buffer_type != BufferType::kDefault) {
612 return false;
613 }
614 if (buf->axis_separators.size()) {
615 return false;
616 }
617 return true;
618}
619
620Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintInlineBufferBind(const Buffer& buffer) {
621 Doc doc;
622 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".Buffer[";
623 if (buffer->shape.size() == 1) {
624 doc << Print(buffer->shape[0]);
625 } else {
626 doc << PrintTuple(buffer->shape.as<ArrayNode>());
627 }
628 doc << ", " << PrintDType(buffer->dtype) << "]";
629 return doc;
630}
631
632// print array out as tuple with parentheses
633Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintTuple(const ArrayNode* op) {
634 Doc doc;
635 doc << '(';
636 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
637 if (i != 0) {
638 doc << ", ";
639 }
640 doc << Print(op->at(i));
641 }
642 if (op->size() == 1) doc << ",";
643 doc << ')';
644 return doc;
645}
646
647Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintCommReducer(const CommReducerNode* op) {
648 Doc doc;
649 int n_var = static_cast<int>(op->rhs.size());
650
651 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".comm_reducer(lambda ";
652 for (const Var& v_lhs : op->lhs) {
653 doc << Print(v_lhs) << ", ";
654 }
655 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
656 doc << Print(op->rhs[i]) << (i == n_var - 1 ? ": " : ", ");
657 }
658 if (n_var == 1) {
659 doc << Print(op->result[0]) << ", ";
660 } else {
661 doc << "(";
662 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
663 doc << Print(op->result[i]);
664 if (i != n_var - 1) {
665 doc << ", ";
666 }
667 }
668 doc << "), ";
669 }
670 doc << Print(op->identity_element) << ")";
671
672 // Remove the vars in `lhs` and `rhs`, because they are the parameters of the printed lambda.
673 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
674 memo_var_.erase(op->lhs[i]);
675 memo_var_.erase(op->rhs[i]);
676 }
677 return doc;
678}
679
680Doc TVMScriptPrinter::Print(const ObjectRef& node) {
681 if (!node.defined()) return Doc::Text("None");
682 if (node->IsInstance<StmtNode>()) {
683 return PrintOptionalInfo(Downcast<Stmt>(node)) << VisitStmt(Downcast<Stmt>(node));
684 } else if (node->IsInstance<PrimExprNode>()) {
685 ExprPrecedence t = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown;
686 return VisitExpr(Downcast<PrimExpr>(node), &t);
687 } else if (node->IsInstance<TypeNode>()) {
688 return VisitType(Downcast<Type>(node));
689 } else if (node->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>()) {
690 return PrintPrimFunc(Downcast<PrimFunc>(node));
691 } else if (node->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>()) {
692 return PrintIRModule(Downcast<IRModule>(node));
693 } else if (node->IsInstance<ArrayNode>()) {
694 return PrintArray(node.as<ArrayNode>());
695 } else if (node->IsInstance<BufferNode>()) {
696 return PrintBuffer(node.as<BufferNode>());
697 } else if (node->IsInstance<StringObj>()) {
698 return PrintString(node.as<StringObj>());
699 } else if (node->IsInstance<IterVarNode>()) {
700 return PrintIterVar(node.as<IterVarNode>());
701 } else if (node->IsInstance<RangeNode>()) {
702 return PrintRange(node.as<RangeNode>());
703 } else if (node->IsInstance<BufferRegionNode>()) {
704 return PrintBufferRegion(node.as<BufferRegionNode>());
705 } else if (node->IsInstance<MatchBufferRegionNode>()) {
706 return PrintMatchBufferRegion(node.as<MatchBufferRegionNode>());
707 } else if (node->IsInstance<CommReducerNode>()) {
708 return PrintCommReducer(node.as<CommReducerNode>());
709 } else if (node->IsInstance<TargetNode>()) {
710 return PrintTarget(node.as<TargetNode>());
711 } else {
712 LOG(FATAL) << "Do not know how to print " << node->GetTypeKey();
713 return Doc();
714 }
715}

755#define TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(OpName, OpString, OpPrecedence) \
756 Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitExpr_(const OpName* op, ExprPrecedence* out_precedence) { \
757 Doc doc; \
758 ExprPrecedence lhs_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown; \
759 ExprPrecedence rhs_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown; \
760 /* Get children expr out_precedence */ \
761 Doc lhs_doc = VisitExpr(op->a, &lhs_precedence); \
762 Doc rhs_doc = VisitExpr(op->b, &rhs_precedence); \
763 ICHECK(lhs_precedence != ExprPrecedence::kUnknown); \
764 ICHECK(rhs_precedence != ExprPrecedence::kUnknown); \
765 /* Update out_precedence of current node. */ \
766 *out_precedence = OpPrecedence; \
767 if (lhs_precedence > OpPrecedence) { \
768 doc << "(" << lhs_doc << ")"; \
769 } else { \
770 doc << lhs_doc; \
771 } \
772 doc << OpString; \
773 if (rhs_precedence >= OpPrecedence) { \
774 doc << "(" << rhs_doc << ")"; \
775 } else { \
776 doc << rhs_doc; \
777 } \
778 return doc; \
779 }

927Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const LetStmtNode* op) {
928 if (!buffer_var_usage_.count(op->var)) {
929 buffer_var_usage_ = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(buffer_var_usage_), op->body);
930 }
931 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = buffer_var_usage_.Get(op->var).value_or({});
932
933 Doc doc;
934 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
935 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".let(" << Print(op->var) << ", " << Print(op->value) << "):";
936 doc << Doc::Indent(
937 4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body));
938 } else {
939 if (memo_var_.find(op->var) == memo_var_.end()) var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->var.get());
940 doc << Print(op->var) << ": " << Print(GetType(op->var)) << " = " << Print(op->value)
941 << Doc::NewLine();
942 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body);
943 }
944 return doc;
945}

947Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* op) {
948 Doc doc;
949 if (op->node.defined()) {
950 // merge attr with realize when possible
951 if (op->node->IsInstance<BufferNode>() && op->attr_key == "realize_scope" &&
952 op->body->IsInstance<BufferRealizeNode>()) {
953 const auto* realize = Downcast<BufferRealize>(op->body).get();
954 if (realize->buffer.same_as(op->node)) {
955 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
956 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".realize(" << Print(realize->buffer)
957 << Print(realize->bounds) << ", " << Print(op->value);
958 if (!is_one(realize->condition)) {
959 doc << ", " << Print(realize->condition);
960 }
961 doc << "):" << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(realize->body));
962 } else {
963 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".realize(" << Print(realize->buffer) << Print(realize->bounds)
964 << ", " << Print(op->value);
965 if (!is_one(realize->condition)) {
966 doc << ", " << Print(realize->condition);
967 }
968 doc << ")" << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(realize->body);
969 }
970 return doc;
971 }
972 }
973 // concise thread env
974 if (op->node->IsInstance<IterVarNode>() &&
975 (op->attr_key == "thread_extent" || op->attr_key == "virtual_thread")) {
976 const auto* iter_var = Downcast<IterVar>(op->node).get();
977 var_not_in_headers_.insert(iter_var->var.get());
978 var_env_map_[iter_var->var] = iter_var->thread_tag;
979 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
980 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".launch_thread(" << Print(iter_var->var) << ", "
981 << Print(op->value) << "):";
982 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
983 } else {
984 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".launch_thread(" << Print(iter_var->var) << ", " << Print(op->value)
985 << ")";
986 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
987 }
988 TryDeallocVar(iter_var->var);
989 return doc;
990 }
991 }
992 // default
993 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
994 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".attr(" << Print(op->node) << ", "
995 << Doc::StrLiteral(op->attr_key) << ", " << Print(op->value) << "):";
996 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
997 } else {
998 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".attr(" << Print(op->node) << ", " << Doc::StrLiteral(op->attr_key)
999 << ", " << Print(op->value) << ")";
1000 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1001 }
1002 return doc;
1003}

1031namespace {
1032struct AllocUsage {
1033 Buffer alloc_buffer;
1034 Array<Buffer> aliasing_buffers;
1035};
1036
1037template <typename AllocNode>
1038AllocUsage FindAllocateUsage(AllocNode* op, Map<Var, Array<Buffer>>* cache_ptr) {
1039 Map<Var, Array<Buffer>>& cache = *cache_ptr;
1040 if (!cache.count(op->buffer_var)) {
1041 cache = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(cache), op->body);
1042 }
1043 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = cache.Get(op->buffer_var).value_or({});
1044
1045 auto is_exact_match = [](Buffer a, Buffer b) {
1046 if (a->dtype != b->dtype) return false;
1047 if (a->shape.size() != b->shape.size()) return false;
1048
1049 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
1050 for (size_t i = 0; i < a->shape.size(); i++) {
1051 if (!analyzer.CanProveEqual(a->shape[i], b->shape[i])) {
1052 return false;
1053 }
1054 }
1055 return true;
1056 };
1057
1058 // If the buffer allocated via T.allocate is an exact match to the
1059 // usage of the buffer later on, then that buffer is the return
1060 // value of T.allocate, and no T.buffer_decl statement is needed.
1061 Buffer alloc_buffer(op->buffer_var, op->dtype, op->extents, {}, 0, op->buffer_var->name_hint, 0,
1062 0, kDefault);
1063 bool found_alloc_buf = false;
1064 Array<Buffer> aliasing_buffers;
1065 for (const auto& buf : buffer_usage) {
1066 if (!found_alloc_buf && is_exact_match(buf, alloc_buffer)) {
1067 alloc_buffer = buf;
1068 found_alloc_buf = true;
1069 } else {
1070 aliasing_buffers.push_back(buf);
1071 }
1072 }
1073
1074 return AllocUsage{alloc_buffer, aliasing_buffers};
1075}
1076} // namespace
1077
1078Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AllocateNode* op) {
1079 auto usage = FindAllocateUsage(op, &buffer_var_usage_);
1080 Buffer& alloc_buffer = usage.alloc_buffer;
1081 Array<Buffer>& aliasing_buffers = usage.aliasing_buffers;
1082 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buffer.get());
1083 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buffer->data.get());
1084
1085 auto storage_scope = GetPtrStorageScope(op->buffer_var);
1086 Doc func_call;
1087 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".allocate(" << Print(op->extents) << ", " << PrintDType(op->dtype)
1088 << ", " << Print(storage_scope);
1089 if (!is_one(op->condition)) {
1090 func_call << ", " << Print(op->condition);
1091 }
1092 if (!op->annotations.empty()) {
1093 func_call << ", annotations={";
1094 func_call << PrintAnnotations(op->annotations);
1095 func_call << "}";
1096 }
1097 func_call << ")";
1098
1099 Doc doc;
1100 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1101 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << Print(alloc_buffer) << ":";
1102 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(aliasing_buffers)
1103 << PrintBody(op->body));
1104 } else {
1105 doc << Print(alloc_buffer) << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1106 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(aliasing_buffers) << PrintBody(op->body);
1107 }
1108 TryDeallocVar(op->buffer_var);
1109 return doc;
1110}
1111
1112Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AllocateConstNode* alloc) {
1113 std::stringstream ss;
1114 ICHECK(alloc->data) << "Should be presented";
1115 const auto& data = alloc->data.value();
1116
1117 if (alloc->dtype.is_int()) {
1118 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 8) {
1119 NDArrayToTIR<int8_t>(data, ss);
1120 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1121 NDArrayToTIR<int16_t>(data, ss);
1122 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1123 NDArrayToTIR<int32_t>(data, ss);
1124 } else {
1125 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1126 }
1127 } else if (alloc->dtype.is_float()) {
1128 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1129 NDArrayToTIR<int16_t>(data, ss);
1130 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1131 NDArrayToTIR<float>(data, ss);
1132 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1133 NDArrayToTIR<double>(data, ss);
1134 } else {
1135 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1136 }
1137 } else {
1138 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1139 }
1140 auto ndarray_str = ss.str();
1141
1142 auto usage = FindAllocateUsage(alloc, &buffer_var_usage_);
1143 Buffer& alloc_buffer = usage.alloc_buffer;
1144 Array<Buffer>& aliasing_buffers = usage.aliasing_buffers;
1145 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buffer.get());
1146 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buffer->data.get());
1147
1148 Doc func_call;
1149 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".allocate_const(" << ndarray_str << ", " << PrintDType(alloc->dtype)
1150 << ", " << Print(alloc->extents) << ")";
1151
1152 Doc doc;
1153 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc->buffer_var.get());
1154 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1155 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << Print(alloc_buffer) << ":";
1156 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(aliasing_buffers)
1157 << PrintBody(alloc->body));
1158 } else {
1159 doc << Print(alloc_buffer) << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1160 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(aliasing_buffers) << PrintBody(alloc->body);
1161 }
1162 return doc;
1163}
1164
1165Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const DeclBufferNode* op) {
1166 const Buffer& buffer = op->buffer;
1167 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buffer.get());
1168 Doc buffer_name = Print(op->buffer);
1169 Doc func_call;
1170 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".decl_buffer(" << memo_buf_decl_.at(buffer) << ")";
1171
1172 Doc doc;
1173 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1174 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << buffer_name << ":";
1175 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1176 } else {
1177 doc << buffer_name << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1178 doc << PrintBody(op->body);
1179 }
1180 return doc;
1181}

1183Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const IfThenElseNode* op) {
1184 Doc doc;
1185 doc << "if " << Print(op->condition) << ":";
1186 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->then_case));
1187 if (!is_one(op->condition) && op->else_case.defined()) {
1188 doc << Doc::NewLine();
1189 doc << "else:" << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->else_case));
1190 }
1191 return doc;
1192}

1195 std::vector<Doc> stmts;
1196 for (Stmt stmt : op->seq) {
1197 stmts.push_back(Print(stmt));
1198 }
1199 return PrintSep(stmts, Doc::NewLine());
1200}

1202Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const EvaluateNode* op) {
1203 if (auto* call = op->value.as<CallNode>()) {
1204 if (call->op.same_as(builtin::assume())) {
1205 Doc doc;
1206 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".assume(" << Print(call->args[0]) << ")";
1207 return doc;
1208 }
1209 }
1210
1211 Doc doc;
1212 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".evaluate(" << Print(op->value) << ")";
1213 return doc;
1214}
1215
1216Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) {
1217 Doc doc;
1218 var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->loop_var.get());
1219 loop_var_map_[op->loop_var.get()] = GetRef<For>(op);
1220 const auto* body = op->body.as<ForNode>();
1221 bool simple_loop = IsSimpleLoop(op);
1222 if (simple_loop) simple_loop_stack_.push_back(GetRef<For>(op));
1223 // It is a loop that can be compressed, let the loops below print it out
1224 if (simple_loop && body != nullptr && IsSimpleLoop(body) && !DependOnPrevLoops(body)) {
1225 doc << Print(GetRef<For>(body));
1226 TryDeallocVar(op->loop_var);
1227 loop_var_map_.erase(op->loop_var.get());
1228 return doc;
1229 }
1230 // It is a loop that can not be compressed
1231 bool print_above = !simple_loop_stack_.empty();
1232 // print loops above if needed
1233 if (print_above) {
1234 doc << PrintLoopStack();
1235 simple_loop_stack_.clear();
1236 }
1237 if (!simple_loop) {
1238 // print current loop if needed
1239 Doc current_loop;
1240 current_loop << PrintLoop(GetRef<For>(op));
1241 current_loop << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1242 doc << (print_above ? Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << current_loop) : current_loop);
1243 } else {
1244 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1245 }
1246 TryDeallocVar(op->loop_var);
1247 loop_var_map_.erase(op->loop_var.get());
1248 return doc;
1249}

1251Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const PrefetchNode* op) {
1252 Doc doc;
1253 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".prefetch(" << Print(op->buffer) << ", " << Print(op->bounds) << ")";
1254 return doc;
1255}

1307
1308/*! Helper functions for block printing. */
1309Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVar(const IterVar& iter_var, const PrimExpr& value) {
1310 Doc doc;
1311 doc << Print(iter_var->var) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".axis.";
1312 switch (iter_var->iter_type) {
1313 case kDataPar:
1314 doc << "spatial";
1315 break;
1316 case kCommReduce:
1317 doc << "reduce";
1318 break;
1319 case kOrdered:
1320 doc << "scan";
1321 break;
1322 case kOpaque:
1323 doc << "opaque";
1324 break;
1325 default:
1326 LOG(FATAL) << "Unknown block var iter type: " << iter_var->iter_type;
1327 break;
1328 }
1329 doc << "(";
1330 const Range& dom = iter_var->dom;
1331 if (is_zero(dom->min)) {
1332 doc << Print(dom->extent);
1333 } else {
1334 doc << "(" << Print(dom->min) << ", " << Print(dom->min + dom->extent) << ")";
1335 }
1336 doc << ", " << Print(value) << ")";
1337 return doc;
1338}
1339
1340Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVarRemaps() {
1341 ICHECK(!block_var_remaps_.empty());
1342 if (block_var_remaps_.size() == 1) {
1343 const IterVar& iter_var = block_var_remaps_[0].first;
1344 const PrimExpr& value = block_var_remaps_[0].second;
1345 return PrintBlockVar(iter_var, value);
1346 }
1347 Doc doc;
1348 std::vector<Doc> iter_vars, iter_values;
1349 std::string iter_type;
1350 for (const auto& pair : block_var_remaps_) {
1351 const IterVar& iter_var = pair.first;
1352 const PrimExpr& value = pair.second;
1353 iter_vars.push_back(Print(iter_var->var));
1354 iter_values.push_back(Print(value));
1355 if (iter_var->iter_type == kDataPar) {
1356 iter_type += "S";
1357 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == kCommReduce) {
1358 iter_type += "R";
1359 } else {
1360 ICHECK(false);
1361 }
1362 }
1363 doc << PrintSep(iter_vars, Doc::Text(", ")) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".axis.remap("
1364 << Doc::StrLiteral(iter_type) << ", [" << PrintSep(iter_values, Doc::Text(", ")) << "])";
1365 return doc;
1366}
1367
1368Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVars(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1369 Doc doc;
1370 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1371 ICHECK_EQ(block_op->iter_vars.size(), op->iter_values.size());
1372 tir::ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
1373
1374 auto is_simple_remap = [this, &expr_equal](const IterVar& iter_var,
1375 const PrimExpr& value) -> bool {
1376 if (iter_var->iter_type != kDataPar && iter_var->iter_type != kCommReduce) return false;
1377 if (!value->IsInstance<VarNode>()) return false;
1378 const Var& var = Downcast<Var>(value);
1379 auto it = loop_var_map_.find(var.get());
1380 return it != loop_var_map_.end() && expr_equal(it->second->min, iter_var->dom->min) &&
1381 expr_equal(it->second->extent, iter_var->dom->extent);
1382 };
1383
1384 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_op->iter_vars.size(); ++i) {
1385 const IterVar& iter_var = block_op->iter_vars[i];
1386 const PrimExpr& value = op->iter_values[i];
1387 var_not_in_headers_.insert(iter_var->var.get());
1388 if (is_simple_remap(iter_var, value)) {
1389 block_var_remaps_.push_back(std::make_pair(iter_var, value));
1390 } else {
1391 if (!block_var_remaps_.empty()) {
1392 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVarRemaps();
1393 block_var_remaps_.clear();
1394 }
1395 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVar(iter_var, value);
1396 }
1397 }
1398 if (!block_var_remaps_.empty()) {
1399 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVarRemaps();
1400 block_var_remaps_.clear();
1401 }
1402 return doc;
1403}
1404
1405Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockAttr(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1406 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1407 Doc block_attr_doc;
1408 // print predicate, binding, read/write tensor region, annotations
1409 if (!is_one(op->predicate)) {
1410 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".where(" << Print(op->predicate) << ")";
1411 }
1412 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".reads("
1413 << PrintExpandedArray(block_op->reads.as<ArrayNode>()) << ")";
1414 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".writes("
1415 << PrintExpandedArray(block_op->writes.as<ArrayNode>()) << ")";
1416 if (!block_op->annotations.empty()) {
1417 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".block_attr({";
1418 block_attr_doc << PrintAnnotations(block_op->annotations);
1419 block_attr_doc << "})";
1420 }
1421 return block_attr_doc;
1422}
1423
1424// This function is to make sure arguments of T.reads() and T.writes() is not parsed by printer as a
1425// List. Therefore the brackets are removed before and after printing arguments out
1426Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintExpandedArray(const ArrayNode* op) {
1427 Doc doc;
1428 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
1429 if (i != 0) {
1430 doc << ", ";
1431 }
1432 doc << Print(op->at(i));
1433 }
1434 return doc;
1435}
1436
1437Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockBody(const BlockNode* op) {
1438 Doc body;
1439 for (const auto& alloc_buf : op->alloc_buffers) {
1440 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buf.get());
1441 body << Print(alloc_buf) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".alloc_buffer("
1442 << memo_buf_decl_[alloc_buf] << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1443 }
1444 for (const auto& match_buf : op->match_buffers) {
1445 body << Print(match_buf) << Doc::NewLine();
1446 }
1447 if (op->init.defined()) {
1448 Doc init_block;
1449 init_block << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".init():";
1450 init_block << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->init.value()));
1451 body << init_block << Doc::NewLine();
1452 }
1453 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1454 return body;
1455}

1457/*!
1458 * \brief Print the name of a block
1459 * \param block_op The block node to be printed
1460 */
1461Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) {
1462 Doc doc;
1463 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".block(";
1464 if (!block_op->name_hint.empty()) {
1465 doc << Doc::StrLiteral(block_op->name_hint);
1466 }
1467 doc << "):";
1468 return doc;
1469}
1470
1471Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1472 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1473 Doc doc = PrintOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(block_op));
1474 // print block name and block vars
1475 doc << PrintBlockName(block_op);
1476 Doc block_var = PrintBlockVars(op);
1477 // print predicate, binding, read/write tensor region, annotations
1478 Doc block_attr_doc = PrintBlockAttr(op);
1479 // print body
1480 Doc body = PrintBlockBody(block_op);
1481 doc << Doc::Indent(4, block_var << block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << body);
1482 for (const auto& iter_var : block_op->iter_vars) {
1483 TryDeallocVar(iter_var->var);
1484 }
1485 return doc;
1486}
1487
1488Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBody(const Stmt& body) {
1489 int memo_num_child, memo_current_num;
1490 std::swap(memo_num_child, num_child_);
1491 std::swap(memo_current_num, current_num_);
1492
1493 Doc doc;
1494 if (body->IsInstance<SeqStmtNode>()) {
1495 const auto& op = Downcast<SeqStmt>(body);
1496 num_child_ = op->seq.size();
1497 current_num_ = 0;
1498 std::vector<Doc> stmts;
1499 for (Stmt stmt : op->seq) {
1500 stmts.push_back(Print(stmt));
1501 current_num_++;
1502 }
1503 doc = PrintSep(stmts, Doc::NewLine());
1504 } else {
1505 num_child_ = 1;
1506 current_num_ = 0;
1507 doc = Print(body);
1508 }
1509
1510 std::swap(memo_num_child, num_child_);
1511 std::swap(memo_current_num, current_num_);
1512 return doc;
1513}

1515Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintIRModule(const IRModule& module) {
1516 auto* op = module.operator->();
1517 Doc doc;
1518 doc << "@tvm.script.ir_module" << Doc::NewLine();
1519 doc << "class Module:";
1520 for (const auto& x : op->functions) {
1521 func2var_[x.second.operator->()] = x.first;
1522 }
1523 Doc body = Doc::NewLine();
1524 std::vector<Doc> functions;
1525 for (auto it = op->functions.begin(); it != op->functions.end(); ++it) {
1526 if ((*it).second.as<PrimFuncNode>()) {
1527 functions.push_back(Print((*it).second));
1528 }
1529 }
1530 body << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintSep(functions, Doc::NewLine() << Doc::NewLine());
1531 body << Doc::NewLine() << DumpMeta();
1532 doc << Doc::Indent(4, body);
1533 return doc;
1534}
1535
1536Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintPrimFunc(const PrimFunc& primFunc) {
1537 auto* op = primFunc.operator->();
1538 // clear renaming map
1539 memo_var_.clear();
1540 memo_buf_.clear();
1541 memo_buf_decl_.clear();
1542 var_not_in_headers_.clear();
1543 buf_not_in_headers_.clear();
1544 // print signature
1545 Doc doc;
1546 doc << "@" << tir_prefix_ << ".prim_func" << Doc::NewLine();
1547 doc << "def " << (func2var_.find(op) == func2var_.end() ? "func" : func2var_[op]->name_hint)
1548 << "(";
1549 std::vector<Doc> params;
1550 std::unordered_set<Buffer, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> simple_buf;
1551 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1552 var_not_in_headers_.insert(param.get());
1553 auto it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1554 // check if this param is a T.handle
1555 if (it != op->buffer_map.end()) {
1556 // check if this match_buffer has only the first two arguments specified
1557 // and whether the match_buffer is a dynamic buffer.
1558 const Buffer& buf = (*it).second;
1559 if (IsSimpleBuffer(buf)) {
1560 simple_buf.insert(buf);
1561 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
1562 params.push_back(Print(buf) << ": " << PrintInlineBufferBind(buf));
1563 continue;
1564 }
1565 }
1566 params.push_back(Print(param) << ": " << Print(GetType(param)));
1567 }
1568 doc << PrintSep(params, Doc::Text(", ")) << ") -> " << Print(primFunc->ret_type) << ":";
1569
1570 Doc body = Doc::NewLine();
1571 // print buffer_bind
1572 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1573 auto it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1574 if (it == op->buffer_map.end()) continue;
1575 const Buffer& buf = (*it).second;
1576 if (simple_buf.count(buf)) continue;
1577 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
1578 body << Print(buf) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".match_buffer(";
1579 ICHECK(memo_buf_decl_.count(buf));
1580 body << Print((*it).first) << ", " << memo_buf_decl_[buf];
1581 body << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1582 }
1583 // print preflattened buffer map
1584 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1585 auto pf_buf_it = op->preflattened_buffer_map.find(param);
1586 if (pf_buf_it != op->preflattened_buffer_map.end()) {
1587 const Buffer& preflattened = (*pf_buf_it).second;
1588
1589 auto buf_it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1590 ICHECK(buf_it != op->buffer_map.end()) << "Found pre-flattened buffer " << preflattened->name
1591 << " with no corresponding post-flatten buffer.";
1592 const Buffer& postflattened = (*buf_it).second;
1593
1594 // Call Print() without assigning in order to fill memo_buf_decl_.
1595 Print(preflattened);
1596 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(preflattened.get());
1597 ICHECK(memo_buf_decl_.count(preflattened));
1598
1599 body << tir_prefix_ << ".preflattened_buffer(" << Print(postflattened) << ", "
1600 << memo_buf_decl_.at(preflattened) << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1601 }
1602 }
1603 // print body
1604 body << "# body" << Doc::NewLine();
1605 if (op->body->IsInstance<BlockRealizeNode>() &&
1606 op->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()->iter_values.empty()) {
1607 const BlockNode* block = op->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()->block.get();
1608 if (block->annotations.empty() && !ContainsOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(block))) {
1609 // Skip print root block
1610 body << "# with " << tir_prefix_ << ".block(\"root\")" << Doc::NewLine();
1611 body << PrintBlockBody(block);
1612 } else {
1613 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1614 }
1615 } else {
1616 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1617 }
1618 // print func attrs
1619 Doc header_attr;
1620 if (primFunc->attrs.defined()) {
1621 header_attr << Doc::NewLine() << "# function attr dict" << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_
1622 << ".func_attr({";
1623 std::vector<Doc> attrs;
1624 for (const auto& it : op->attrs->dict) {
1625 attrs.push_back(Doc::StrLiteral(it.first) << ": " << Print(it.second));
1626 }
1627 header_attr << PrintSep(attrs, Doc::Text(", ")) << "})";
1628 }
1629 // print buffer declarations(buffers not defined by buffer_bind or buffer_allocate)
1630 Doc header_buf;
1631 std::vector<const BufferNode*> bufs;
1632 for (const auto& it : memo_buf_) {
1633 if (buf_not_in_headers_.find(it.first.get()) == buf_not_in_headers_.end()) {
1634 bufs.push_back(it.first.get());
1635 }
1636 }
1637 if (!bufs.empty()) {
1638 header_buf << Doc::NewLine() << "# buffer definition";
1639 std::sort(bufs.begin(), bufs.end(), [&](const BufferNode* a, const BufferNode* b) {
1640 return memo_buf_[GetRef<Buffer>(a)].str() < memo_buf_[GetRef<Buffer>(b)].str();
1641 });
1642 for (const auto& buf : bufs) {
1643 header_buf << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Buffer>(buf)) << " = " << tir_prefix_
1644 << ".buffer_decl(";
1645 header_buf << memo_buf_decl_[GetRef<Buffer>(buf)] << ")";
1646 }
1647 }
1648 // print var declaration
1649 Doc header_var;
1650 std::vector<const VarNode*> vars;
1651 for (const auto& it : memo_var_) {
1652 if (var_not_in_headers_.find(it.first.get()) == var_not_in_headers_.end()) {
1653 vars.push_back(it.first.get());
1654 }
1655 }
1656 if (!var_env_map_.empty()) {
1657 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << "# var definition";
1658 for (const auto& it : var_env_map_) {
1659 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(it.first) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".env_thread("
1660 << Doc::StrLiteral(it.second) << ")";
1661 }
1662 }
1663 if (!vars.empty()) {
1664 std::sort(vars.begin(), vars.end(), [&](const VarNode* a, const VarNode* b) {
1665 return memo_var_[GetRef<Var>(a)].str() < memo_var_[GetRef<Var>(b)].str();
1666 });
1667 for (const auto& var : vars) {
1668 auto type = GetRef<Var>(var)->type_annotation;
1669 if (auto* ptr_type = type.as<PointerTypeNode>()) {
1670 auto* prim_type = ptr_type->element_type.as<PrimTypeNode>();
1671 ICHECK(prim_type);
1672 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Var>(var)) << " = " << tir_prefix_
1673 << ".buffer_var(";
1674 header_var << PrintDType(prim_type->dtype) << ", "
1675 << Doc::StrLiteral(ptr_type->storage_scope) << ")";
1676 } else {
1677 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Var>(var)) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".var(";
1678 header_var << PrintDType(var->dtype) << ")";
1679 }
1680 }
1681 }
1682 doc << Doc::Indent(4, header_attr << header_var << header_buf << body);
1683 return doc;
1684}

1720
1721Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBufferIndices(const Array<PrimExpr>& indices) {
1722 Doc doc;
1723 doc << '[';
1724 for (size_t i = 0; i < indices.size(); ++i) {
1725 if (i != 0) {
1726 doc << ", ";
1727 }
1728 PrimExpr index = indices[i];
1729 if (const RampNode* ramp = index.as<RampNode>()) {
1730 // specify ramp printing as python index slice
1731 if (auto* stride_imm = ramp->stride.as<IntImmNode>()) {
1732 doc << Print(ramp->base) << ":" << Print(ramp->base + ramp->lanes * ramp->stride);
1733 if (stride_imm->value != 1) {
1734 doc << ":" << Print(ramp->stride);
1735 }
1736 continue;
1737 }
1738 }
1739 doc << Print(index);
1740 }
1741 doc << ']';
1742 return doc;
1743}

1749 << memo_buf_decl_[buf_usage] << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1750 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf_usage.get());
1751 }
1752 return decls;
1753}

1755Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBufferRegion(const BufferRegionNode* op) {
1756 Doc doc;
1757 if (op->region.size() == 0) {
1758 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[()]";
1759 } else {
1760 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[";
1761 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->region.size(); ++i) {
1762 if (i != 0) doc << ", ";
1763 const auto& range = op->region[i];
1764 if (!is_one(range->extent)) {
1765 doc << Print(range->min) << " : " << Print(ana_.Simplify(range->min + range->extent));
1766 } else {
1767 doc << Print(range->min);
1768 }
1769 }
1770 doc << "]";
1771 }
1772 return doc;
1773}
1774
1775Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintAnnotations(const Map<String, ObjectRef>& annotations) {
1776 Doc res;
1777 std::vector<std::pair<String, ObjectRef>> anno_list;
1778 anno_list.reserve(annotations.size());
1779 for (const auto& pair : annotations) {
1780 anno_list.emplace_back(pair);
1781 }
1782 sort(anno_list.begin(), anno_list.end());
1783 for (size_t i = 0; i < anno_list.size(); ++i) {
1784 if (i != 0) {
1785 res << ", ";
1786 }
1787 res << "\"" << anno_list[i].first << "\":" << Print(anno_list[i].second);
1788 }
1789 return res;
1790}
1791
1792Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoop(const For& loop) {
1793 Doc res;
1794 res << "for " << Print(loop->loop_var) << " in " << tir_prefix_
1795 << "." + std::string(ForKind2String(loop->kind)) + "(";
1796 if (is_zero(loop->min)) {
1797 res << Print(loop->extent);
1798 } else {
1799 res << Print(loop->min) << ", " << Print(ana_.Simplify(loop->min + loop->extent));
1800 }
1801 if (loop->thread_binding.defined()) {
1802 res << ", thread=";
1803 res << Print(loop->thread_binding.value()->thread_tag);
1804 }
1805 if (!loop->annotations.empty()) {
1806 res << ", annotations={";
1807 res << PrintAnnotations(loop->annotations);
1808 res << "}";
1809 }
1810 res << "):";
1811 return res;
1812}
1813
1814Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoopStack() {
1815 Doc res;
1816 if (simple_loop_stack_.size() == 1) {
1817 res << PrintLoop(simple_loop_stack_[0]);
1818 } else if (simple_loop_stack_.size() > 1) {
1819 std::vector<Doc> vars, extents;
1820 for (const auto& loop : simple_loop_stack_) {
1821 vars.push_back(Print(loop->loop_var));
1822 extents.push_back(Print(loop->extent));
1823 }
1824 res << "for " << PrintSep(vars, Doc::Text(", ")) << " in " << tir_prefix_ << ".grid("
1825 << PrintSep(extents, Doc::Text(", ")) << "):";
1826 }
1827 return res;
1828}
1829
1830Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintTarget(const TargetNode* target) {
1831 Doc res;
1832 res << tir_prefix_ << ".target({";
1833 Map<String, ObjectRef> config = target->Export();
1834 for (auto it = config.begin(); it != config.end(); ++it) {
1835 if (it != config.begin()) {
1836 res << ", ";
1837 }
1838 res << "\"" << (*it).first << "\":";
1839 if ((*it).first == "host") {
1840 ICHECK(target->host.defined());
1841 res << PrintTarget(target->GetHost().value().get());
1842 } else {
1843 res << Print((*it).second);
1844 }
1845 }
1846 res << "})";
1847 return res;
1848}

1851 * \brief The printer for TVMScript with diagnostic
1852 * \details The printer obtain the precedence of the top-level operation when printing each
1853 * subexpression to decide whether or not parentheses is needed.

1855class TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic : public TVMScriptPrinter {

1857 explicit TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic(const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
1858 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate)
1859 : TVMScriptPrinter(tir_prefix, show_meta, annotate) {}
1860
1861 protected:
1862 Doc PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) override;

1867Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) {

1869 doc << PrintUnderline(GetRef<Stmt>(block_op), doc.str().size());

1873Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintUnderline(const Stmt& stmt, int length) {
1874 Doc doc;
1875 // annotation
1876 if (ContainsOptionalInfo(stmt)) {
1877 String underline = std::string(length, '^');
1878 doc << Doc::NewLine() << underline;
1879 }
1880 return doc;
1881}

1889String AsTVMScript(const ObjectRef& mod, const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta) {
1890 ICHECK(mod->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>() || mod->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>());
1891 Doc doc;
1892 doc << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintHeader(tir_prefix)
1893 << TVMScriptPrinter(tir_prefix, show_meta).Print(mod);
1894 return doc.str() + "\n";
1895}

1897TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("script.AsTVMScript").set_body_typed(AsTVMScript);

1899String AsTVMScriptWithDiagnostic(const ObjectRef& mod, const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
1900 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate) {
1901 ICHECK(mod->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>() || mod->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>());
1902 Doc doc;

1904 << TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic(tir_prefix, show_meta, annotate).Print(mod);
